### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Lifecycle e2e smoke test
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Boot locally with:
###   make up-dataplane
### Then run these requests in order.

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8080
@correlationId = test-http-lifecycle-001
@configId = replace-with-config-id

### 1. Create draft
POST {{baseUrl}}/configctl/configs
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

{
  "name": "orders-prod",
  "format": "json",
  "content": "{\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"Orders Prod\",\"description\":\"minimal lifecycle smoke config\"},\"bindings\":[{\"name\":\"orders\",\"topic\":\"sales.order.created\"}],\"fields\":[{\"name\":\"order_id\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true},{\"name\":\"status\",\"type\":\"string\",\"required\":true}],\"rules\":[{\"name\":\"order_id_required\",\"field\":\"order_id\",\"operator\":\"required\",\"severity\":\"error\"},{\"name\":\"status_not_empty\",\"field\":\"status\",\"operator\":\"not_empty\",\"severity\":\"error\"}]}"
}

###

### 2. Validate draft
POST {{baseUrl}}/configctl/config-versions/{{configId}}/validate
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 3. Compile
POST {{baseUrl}}/configctl/config-versions/{{configId}}/compile
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

{}

###

### 4. Activate
POST {{baseUrl}}/configctl/config-versions/{{configId}}/activate
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

{
  "scope_kind": "global",
  "scope_key": "default"
}

###

### 5. Confirm active config in configctl
GET {{baseUrl}}/configctl/configs/active?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 6. Confirm configctl runtime projections expose the canonical active runtime state
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/configctl/projections?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 7. Confirm validator runtime cache was updated
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/validator/active?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 8. Confirm ingestion runtime bindings projected by configctl
###    The response should expose the active bindings plus the compact runtime set
###    for the same activation, which is what bootstraps consumer/emulator.
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/ingestion/bindings?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 9. Confirm validation results produced from the data plane
###    Wait a few seconds after activation if needed; the emulator publishes
###    both a valid and an invalid sample for each active binding.
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/validator/results?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default&limit=10
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

###

### 10. Confirm aggregated validation incidents for the active scope
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/validator/incidents?scope_kind=global&scope_key=default&limit=10
Accept: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}
